should i run the local or java citrix ica client stanford answers stanford university stanford answers should i run the local or java citrix ica client categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home should i run the local or java citrix ica client search this site the local client is recommended for most users to select the local client these directions assume that you have already successfully installed a citrix client on your computer log in to myapps click settings in the applications window click client preferences select local client from the client type drop down list click ok the local client maps your default printer and your computer's local drive to your myapps session click return to go back to the applications window tip if you select a client that is not suitable you will be prompted to save an ica file if this occurs cancel the prompt and select a different client note the java client is not available through the myapps site the activex control embedded client is no longer available this option was removed by citrix with the release of version 10 of the windows citrix client in april 2007 citrix stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
